## 1. Protocol Architecture Overview

| Dimension | Claude Code / MCP | OpenCode |
|-----------|-------------------|----------|
| **Runtime** | Node.js CLI (`dist/index.js`) | Bun runtime (`bun`) |
| **Tool Protocol** | MCP (Model Context Protocol) via `.mcp.json` JSON Schema | Bun tools via `@opencode-ai/plugin` TypeScript objects |
| **Command Protocol** | Slash commands via `commands/*.md` (YAML frontmatter + Markdown) | Command docs via `.opencode/commands/*.md` (YAML frontmatter + Markdown) |
| **Lifecycle Protocol** | `hooks/hooks.json` (JSON command definitions) | `plugins/*.ts` (TypeScript `Plugin` exports with event handlers) |
| **Package Manager** | NPM (root `package.json`) | Bun (`.opencode/package.json` depends on `@opencode-ai/plugin@1.14.20`) |
| **Plugin Metadata** | `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` + `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json` | No separate metadata file; plugins are just TypeScript modules |
| **Tool Count** | 4 MCP tools | 9 Bun tools |
| **Command Count** | 10 slash commands | 10 command docs |

---

## 2. Tool Definitions: MCP vs Bun Tool

### 2.1 MCP Tool Definition (`.mcp.json`)

**File:** `/Users/ubuntu/1-project/idea0015-trae-plugin-cc/.mcp.json`

**JSON Schema Definition:**

The `.mcp.json` file has a single top-level key `tools` containing an array of tool objects. Each tool object follows this schema:

```typescript
interface McpTool {
  name: string;                    // Tool identifier (e.g., "trae_run")
  description: string;             // Human-readable description
  parameters: {
    type: "object";
    properties: Record<string, {
      type: "string" | "boolean" | "integer" | "array";
      description: string;
      default?: any;               // Optional default value
      enum?: string[];             // Optional enum constraint
      items?: { type: string };    // For arrays: item type
    }>;
    required?: string[];           // Required field names
  };
}
```

**Actual Example -- `trae_run` tool:**

```json
{
  "name": "trae_run",
  "description": "使用 Trae Agent 执行任意自然语言任务...",
  "parameters": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "prompt":       { "type": "string", "description": "任务描述" },
      "resume":       { "type": "string", "description": "恢复会话..." },
      "session_id":   { "type": "string", "description": "指定新会话 ID" },
      "yolo":         { "type": "boolean", "description": "YOLO 模式..." },
      "allowed_tools": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" }, "description": "..." },
      "disallowed_tools": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" }, "description": "..." },
      "json_output":  { "type": "boolean", "description": "返回结构化 JSON 输出" },
      "background":   { "type": "boolean", "description": "后台执行" },
      "worktree":     { "type": "string", "description": "在隔离的 git worktree 中工作..." },
      "query_timeout": { "type": "string", "description": "单次查询超时..." },
      "bash_tool_timeout": { "type": "string", "description": "Bash 工具超时" },
      "inject_context": { "type": "string", "description": "注入指定会话的上下文..." }
    },
    "required": ["prompt"]
  }
}
```

**All 4 MCP tools defined:**
| Tool Name | Parameters Count | Required Params |
|-----------|-----------------|-----------------|
| `trae_run` | 12 | `prompt` |
| `trae_review` | 6 | (none) |
| `trae_sessions` | 4 | (none) |
| `trae_acp` | 5 | (none) |

### 2.2 OpenCode Bun Tool Definition

**TypeScript Type (from `@opencode-ai/plugin/dist/tool.d.ts`):**

```typescript
// Exact type from the SDK:
export type ToolContext = {
    sessionID: string;
    messageID: string;
    agent: string;
    directory: string;       // Current project directory
    worktree: string;        // Project worktree root
    abort: AbortSignal;
    metadata(input: { title?: string; metadata?: Record<string, any> }): void;
    ask(input: AskInput): Effect.Effect<void>;
};

export type ToolResult = string | {
    output: string;
    metadata?: Record<string, any>;
};

export declare function tool<Args extends z.ZodRawShape>(input: {
    description: string;
    args: Args;                                              // Zod schema object
    execute(args: z.infer<z.ZodObject<Args>>, context: ToolContext): Promise<ToolResult>;
}): { description: string; args: Args; execute(...): Promise<ToolResult> };

export declare namespace tool {
    var schema: typeof z;   // Zod itself — tool.schema === z
}

export type ToolDefinition = ReturnType<typeof tool>;
```

**Actual Example -- `trae-run.ts`:**

```typescript
import { tool } from "@opencode-ai/plugin"
import { $ } from "bun"
import path from "path"

const PLUGIN_DIR = path.dirname(path.dirname(import.meta.dir))
const DIST_INDEX = path.join(PLUGIN_DIR, "dist", "index.js")

export default tool({
  description: "使用 Trae Agent 执行任意自然语言任务...",
  args: {
    prompt: tool.schema.string().describe("任务描述"),
    resume: tool.schema.string().optional().describe("恢复会话..."),
    session_id: tool.schema.string().optional().describe("指定新会话 ID"),
    yolo: tool.schema.boolean().optional().describe("YOLO 模式..."),
    allowed_tools: tool.schema.array(tool.schema.string()).optional().describe("..."),
    disallowed_tools: tool.schema.array(tool.schema.string()).optional().describe("..."),
    json_output: tool.schema.boolean().optional().describe("返回结构化 JSON 输出"),
    background: tool.schema.boolean().optional().describe("后台执行"),
    worktree: tool.schema.string().optional().describe("在隔离的 git worktree 中工作..."),
    query_timeout: tool.schema.string().optional().describe("单次查询超时..."),
    bash_tool_timeout: tool.schema.string().optional().describe("Bash 工具超时"),
    inject_context: tool.schema.string().optional().describe("注入指定会话的上下文..."),
  },
  async execute(args, context) {
    const cliArgs: string[] = ["node", DIST_INDEX, "run"]
    cliArgs.push(args.prompt)
    if (args.resume) cliArgs.push("--resume", args.resume)
    // ... (more args)
    const result = await $`${cliArgs}`.cwd(PLUGIN_DIR)
    if (result.exitCode !== 0 && result.stderr) {
      process.stderr.write(result.stderr)
    }
    return { text: result.stdout }
  },
})
```

**All 9 Bun tools defined:**
| File | Tool Name (inferred from key in Hooks.tool) | Args Count | Has Required Args |
|------|---------------------------------------------|------------|-------------------|
| `trae-run.ts` | (default export) | 12 | `prompt` |
| `trae-setup.ts` | (default export) | 0 | No |
| `trae-review.ts` | (default export) | 6 | No |
| `trae-sessions.ts` | (default export) | 5 | `action` (enum) |
| `trae-acp.ts` | (default export) | 5 | `action` (enum) |
| `trae-status.ts` | (default export) | 0 | No |
| `trae-result.ts` | (default export) | 1 | `task_id` |
| `trae-cancel.ts` | (default export) | 1 | `task_id` |
| `trae-rescue.ts` | (default export) | 1 | No (`context` is optional) |

### 2.3 Key Structural Differences

| Aspect | MCP (`.mcp.json`) | OpenCode Bun Tool (`tool({})`) |
|--------|-------------------|-------------------------------|
| **Format** | Pure JSON | TypeScript object via `tool()` factory |
| **Schema Language** | JSON Schema (`type`, `properties`, `required`, `enum`, `items`) | Zod v4 (`tool.schema.string()`, `.optional()`, `.describe()`, `.default()`, `.enum()`) |
| **Required fields** | `"required": ["fieldName"]` array | No `.optional()` chain (non-optional Zod fields are required by default) |
| **Default values** | `"default": value` in property | `.default(value)` on Zod schema (see `limit` in `trae-sessions.ts`) |
| **Array typing** | `"type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" }` | `tool.schema.array(tool.schema.string())` |
| **Enum support** | `"enum": ["list", "detail", ...]` | `tool.schema.enum(["list", "detail", ...])` |
| **Description** | `"description": "..."` in property | `.describe("...")` chain method |
| **Execution function** | None (handled externally by Claude Code via subprocess) | `async execute(args, context) => Promise<ToolResult>` — required |
| **Return type** | Implicitly stdout text from subprocess | `{ text: string }` or `{ output: string; metadata?: Record }` or `string` |
| **Context access** | None (no session/context info available) | `context: ToolContext` with `sessionID`, `messageID`, `agent`, `directory`, `worktree`, `abort`, `metadata()`, `ask()` |
| **Abort support** | None | `context.abort: AbortSignal` |

