## 6. Execution Model Comparison

### 6.1 MCP Execution

```
Claude Code Agent
  |-- calls MCP tool "trae_run" with JSON args
  |
  v
Claude Code MCP client
  |-- Spawns: node dist/index.js run --prompt "..." --yolo --background ...
  |-- Passes args as CLI flags
  |-- Captures stdout/stderr
  |-- Returns stdout as text response
  v
dist/index.js (CLI entry point)
  |-- Parses argv
  |-- Calls appropriate handler in src/commands/run.ts
  |-- Spawns trae-cli as child process
  v
trae-cli (external)
```

**Communication protocol:** Subprocess with CLI arguments as strings. Output is stdout plain text.

### 6.2 OpenCode Bun Tool Execution

```
OpenCode Agent (LLM)
  |-- Decides to call tool
  |
  v
OpenCode tool runner
  |-- Validates args against Zod schema (COMPILE-TIME)
  |-- Calls execute(args, context) directly
  |
  v
execute() function in trae-run.ts
  |-- Builds CLI args array: ["node", "dist/index.js", "run", ...]
  |-- Spawns: Bun.$`node dist/index.js run --prompt "..." --yolo ...`
  |-- Returns { text: result.stdout }
  v
dist/index.js (CLI entry point)
  |-- Same as above
  v
trae-cli (external)
```

**Communication protocol:** Direct TypeScript function call -> subprocess spawn via Bun's `$` shell.

### 6.3 Execution Model Comparison

| Aspect | MCP Tools | OpenCode Bun Tools |
|--------|-----------|-------------------|
| **Invocation** | Claude Code spawns `node dist/index.js <cmd> [flags]` | OpenCode calls `execute(args, context)` directly, which then spawns |
| **Argument passing** | CLI flags (`--prompt "value"`, `--yolo`, `--allowed-tool Bash`) | Structured object `args: { prompt: string, yolo: boolean, ... }` |
| **Subprocess layer** | 1 layer: Claude Code -> dist/index.js | 2 layers: OpenCode -> execute() -> dist/index.js |
| **Shell API** | `child_process.spawn` (Node.js, used by Claude Code internally) | `Bun.$` template literal shell (Bun-specific) |
| **Working directory** | Determined by Claude Code session context | `PLUGIN_DIR` (computed from `import.meta.dir`) |
| **Streaming** | Not supported (stdout captured as text) | Supported via `process.stderr.write()` and stdout buffering |
| **Cancellation** | Claude Code manages subprocess lifecycle | `context.abort: AbortSignal` available but not used |

